From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: hotdog local experiment <hotdog-local@example.invalid>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: hotdog: add early PSCI reset entry probe

This patch is intentionally destructive for normal boot: it turns the arm64
primary entry path into an immediate PSCI SYSTEM_RESET request.

Use it only for a dedicated mainline probe image. If the bootloader branches
into the kernel, the phone should reset quickly through PSCI `smc #0`. If the
phone still hangs with no reset/USB/fastboot return, the failure is likely
before `primary_entry`, in the bootloader handoff, or in a very early exception
around the SMC itself.

The stock and mainline SM8150 DTs both advertise PSCI method "smc"; the stock
entry12 DTB pack also contains `compatible = "arm,psci-1.0"; method = "smc";`.
---
 arch/arm64/kernel/head.S | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S b/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S
--- a/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S
+++ b/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S
@@ -96,1 +96,20 @@
 SYM_CODE_START(primary_entry)
+	/*
+	 * Hotdog early-entry probe.
+	 *
+	 * PSCI_0_2_FN_SYSTEM_RESET = 0x84000009. The stock DTB pack and the
+	 * mainline sm8150.dtsi both describe PSCI as SMC, so this should reset
+	 * the phone immediately if the bootloader reaches primary_entry.
+	 *
+	 * Do not ship this in a bootable kernel. It is a one-shot diagnostic
+	 * for distinguishing "bootloader never entered the kernel" from
+	 * "kernel entered but hangs before initramfs/pstore/USB".
+	 */
+	movz	x0, #0x0009
+	movk	x0, #0x8400, lsl #16
+	mov	x1, xzr
+	mov	x2, xzr
+	mov	x3, xzr
+	smc	#0
+0:	wfe
+	b	0b
